    <a name="basics"></a>
    <h3>Basics</h3>
    <p>
      <ul>
        <li>Make sure all airports and waypoints are in ICAO format</li>
        <li>Upload a .CSV file</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p>
      Because we support the entire world, you'll need to use ICAO identifiers. A lot of IATA identifiers have the same name as navagation aids, like VORs or NDBs, so your map will look strange if you try to use IATA codes or shorthand codes.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you fly from a strip that isn't on the site, send us a message from your profile page with the info on the strip and we'll add it. Even if it's a private farm or back country strip.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you use a logbook that isn't supported yet, go to your profile page and click the "Message Us" button and request it. New logbooks are added within a day usually.
    </p>
    <p>
      Questions? Comments? Ideas? Send a message by clicking the "Message Us" button on your profile page.
    </p>

    <hr>
    <a name="spreadsheet"></a>
    <h4>Uploading from a Spreadsheet</h4>
    <p>
      If you keep your logbook as a spreadsheet in excell or a similar program, you can save or export it as a CSV file and upload it using the foreflight option as long as your spreadsheet conforms to the following example:

      <br>
        <%= image_tag 'foreflight_example.png' %>
      <br>
      Here is a <%= link_to 'template file', 'foreflight_template.csv', download: '', class: 'dark-link' %> to use.

      <p>
        The headers are optional, but the order and spacing is important. So, for example, if you don't include AircraftID, leave that column blank, don't remove it.
      </p>
      <p>
        The only required fields are:
        <ul>
          <li>
            Date
          </li>
          <li>
            From
          </li>
          <li>
            To
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </p>
    <p>
      REMEMBER. You have to save or export the file as a CSV file. You can't import an .xls, .xlsx, or .numbers file.
    </p>

